Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in addBinding in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: addBinding in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3 has an integer overflow.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in build_model in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: build_model in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3 has an integer overflow.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in defineAttribute in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: defineAttribute in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3 has an integer overflow.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: integer overflow in function XML_GetBuffer
Vulnerabilities.Description: Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.4 has a signed integer overflow in XML_GetBuffer, for configurations with a nonzero XML_CONTEXT_BYTES.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: integer overflow in the doProlog function
Vulnerabilities.Description: Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.4 has an integer overflow in the doProlog function.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Large number of prefixed XML attributes on a single tag can crash libexpat
Vulnerabilities.Description: In Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3, a left shift by 29 (or more) places in the storeAtts function in xmlparse.c can lead to realloc misbehavior (e.g., allocating too few bytes, or only freeing memory).

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in doProlog in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: In doProlog in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3, an integer overflow exists for m_groupSize.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in lookup in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: lookup in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3 has an integer overflow.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in nextScaffoldPart in xmlparse.c
Vulnerabilities.Description: nextScaffoldPart in xmlparse.c in Expat (aka libexpat) before 2.4.3 has an integer overflow.

Vulnerabilities.Title: expat: Integer overflow in storeAtts in xmlparse.c
